HEADWORD: Suretyship
<hw>Sure"ty*ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of being surety; the
obligation of a person to answer for the debt, default, or miscarriage
of another.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

